description: Human-readable description of the reported attribute, including commodity type and a description of what is being recorded.
Date associated with the value (e.g., for ESR variables, it represents the sales week end). See the ATTRIBUTES table for more details.
Unit of measurement for the reported value (ex. Metric Tons).
A unique identifier for a country joinable to the GEOGRAPHY_INDEX table.
Unique identifier for a variable, which defines the USDA dataset that the data originates (e.g., ESR - Export Sales Report), the commodity associated with that variable, and what is being measured.

The marketing year tied to the agricultural seasons and harvest periods of a specific crop. A marketing year typically begins in the month when a particular crop's harvest starts and ends just before the next year's harvest begin. This period can vary significantly between different crops and different countries.
Calendar year associated with the value.
